1. Sign up and config

   a. Create a Githut account:  https://github.com/
   b. Insstall Git to your own PC: https://git-scm.com/downloads

   c. Config:

      * Set your username for every repository:

	  $ git config --global user.name <your_user_name_here>

      * Set your email (same email as your Github account)

	  $ git config --global user.email <your email>

      * Check Git Config:

	  $ git config --list

2. Git Init
   a. Create a local Repo in your own PC:

      $ git init

   b. Create a repository in GitHub:

      Click on "Create repository" button.

   b. Link the local repository to an empty Github repository:

      $ git remote add origin [Github_Repo_URL]

3. Git Add - Add changes to Staging Area

     $ git status
     $ git add file_name
     $ git add .          //add all changes to staging area

4. Git Commit - Push changes to Local Repo

     $ git commit -m "Commit_Message"

     $ git commit --amend -m "Commit_Message_Update"



4. Git Commit - Push changes to Local Repo

     $ git commit -m "Commit_Message"

     $ git commit --amend -m "Commit_Message_Update"


